// @run
// @log 1
// @log a
// A10 stage 2 (generics over arrays): `T` is inferred from the argument array's
// element type. `first<T>(xs: T[]): T` returns `xs[0]`; the element type flows
// from the array literal into `T`, monomorphizing per call site (i32, string).
function first<T>(xs: T[]): T xs[0]
print(first([1, 2, 3]))
print(first(["a", "b"]))
